Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 - 12/2018]
Title: EXTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: REAR BUMPER: REASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2018 MY Prius [11/2015 - 12/2018]

REASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. INSTALL REAR BUMPER ARM SUB-ASSEMBLY LH

(a) Install the rear bumper arm sub-assembly LH with the 4 bolts.

Torque:

18 N·m {184 kgf·cm, 13 ft·lbf}

2. INSTALL REAR BUMPER ARM SUB-ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

3. INSTALL NO. 1 REAR BUMPER REINFORCEMENT

(a) Install the No. 1 rear bumper reinforcement with the 6 bolts.

Torque:

34 N·m {347 kgf·cm, 25 ft·lbf}

4. INSTALL REAR BUMPER SIDE SEAL LH

(a) Install the 3 clips.

*1

Rear Bumper Side Clip

(b) Install the rear bumper side seal LH with the rear bumper side clip.

5. INSTALL REAR BUMPER SIDE SEAL RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

6. INSTALL REAR BUMPER SIDE RETAINER LH

(a) Engage the claw as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction (1)

Install in this Direction (2)

(b) Engage the guide as shown in the illustration.

(c) Engage the 3 clips as shown in the illustration to install the rear bumper side retainer LH.

Install in this Direction

7. INSTALL REAR BUMPER SIDE RETAINER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

8. INSTALL NO. 3 REAR BUMPER PAD

HINT:

When installing the No. 3 rear bumper pad, heat the rear bumper assembly using a heat light.

Heating Temperature

Item

Temperature

Rear Bumper Assembly

40 to 60°C (104 to 140°F)

CAUTION:

  • Do not touch the heat light and heated parts, touching the heat light may result in burns.
  • Touching heated parts for a long time may result in burns.

*a

Heated Part

*b

Heat Light

NOTICE:

Do not heat the rear bumper assembly excessively.

(a) Clean the rear bumper assembly surface.

(1) Using a heat light, heat the rear bumper assembly surface.

(2) Remove the double-sided tape from the rear bumper assembly.

(3) Wipe off any tape adhesive residue with cleaner.

(b) Remove the release paper from a new No. 3 rear bumper pad.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(c) Install the No. 3 rear bumper pad as shown in the illustration.

HINT:

  • Install the No. 3 rear bumper pad along the line on the rear bumper cover.
  • Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

*a

Line

18. INSTALL NO. 3 LUGGAGE ROOM WIRE

(a) w/o Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Engage the 7 clamps to install the No. 3 luggage room wire.

(b) w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Engage the 12 clamps to install the No. 3 luggage room wire.
